{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"65d8bd90-2d2c-46a9-ae0c-a787ac9c9fe5","content":"The bug is on line 29: `ProcessPayment` only checks `amount == 0` but not negative values. The fastest iteration workflow is **`dotnet watch test`** — it auto-reruns tests on every file save.\n\nLet me set it up and fix the bug:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01L7UR9aCiw7xDJdAMUXarfk","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Setting up watch workflow"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_012ikhwxHYetUuCsTDkqGfAf","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/sv-9ed3239960264580bd1465c387d4f363 && dotnet watch test --filter \"ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\" 2>&1","description":"Start dotnet watch test for the failing test","mode":"async","shellId":"watch"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Start dotnet watch test for the failing test"}],"interactionId":"1ecc39b4-219d-4228-89d3-1de1cd513043","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The bug is clear: `ProcessPayment` only checks for `amount == 0` but doesn't check for negative amounts. The test on line 24 expects an `ArgumentException` for `-50.00m`, but the method just returns `true`.\n\nThe user wants the fastest workflow. The answer is `dotnet watch test` — it watches for file changes and re-runs tests automatically, no manual rebuild needed.\n\nLet me start `dotnet watch test` in async mode, then fix the bug, and show the workflow.","outputTokens":390,"requestId":"A7C6:F1259:2BB17D:2EE826:6A034B82"},"id":"42878197-a286-44fd-9e11-eca9c30b6984","timestamp":"2026-05-12T15:47:22.467Z","parentId":"35a3a203-c907-40a9-94a7-d1cae2a70da2"}
